            {
                "s2_paper_id": "58c0d02eb8a960e5047bd20e728d316e2eeaed8a",
                "title": "Prevalence of 12 Common Health Conditions in Sexual and Gender Minority Participants in the All of Us Research Program",
                "year": 2023,
                "venue": "JAMA Network Open",
                "citation_count": 39,
                "reference_count": 51,
                "abstract": "Key Points Question Is the prevalence of certain health conditions higher among sexual and gender minority (SGM) people in the US compared with cisgender and heterosexual (non-SGM) people? Findings In this cross-sectional study of 30\u2009763 SGM and 316\u2009105 non-SGM adults enrolled in the All of Us Research Program, the odds of 8 health conditions were significantly higher in at least 1 of 6 SGM groups compared with their non-SGM counterparts. Meaning The findings of this study suggest that there are disparities for certain health conditions among SGM adults compared with their non-SGM counterparts.",
